> this comm as "edited but not up yet." Here are a few things that need
> to be
> done to it before we can load it. Since this comm is not loaded, to
> "look at"
> something, you'll need to examine the files in C.ng/bennassuti.

Steve, this will be a long reply.  My guess is you should save it
somewhere that any eventual Bennassuti editor will surely see it, maybe
even in HISTORY.

First of all, I was wrong in June 1995: Benn. has NOT been edited.  He
was typed in by that group in Ireland and they did their usual good job.
However, there seem to be lots of errors in spacing, in particular
around apostrophes, and their are some typos (e.g., in Inf. I, which I
looked over _fairly_ carefully only, I noted "chiundo" [ = chiudendo],
Marome [ = Marone], memesimo [ = medesimo].  In short, there are enough
infelicities that we need to have a regular edit of the text before we
put it up.  When this might be, I don't know.  And so I think we need to
leave Benn. for another day.  The one insuperable difficulty is that
Benn.'s numbers are NOT line nos. in the poem, but the number of his
note (i.e., note 15 is not the note to verse 15, but the 15th subject he
chooses to address, and might be anywhere from verse 6 to 80).  Thus
these all have to be reinterpreted (not difficult, but time-consuming
when 100 cantos are at stake) before the texts will display correctly.
> 
> 1. Desc file needs to be completed with author name, publisher info,
> etc. Can
> you do this?

Yes, I have done so, leaving (for obvious reasons) the "editor" entry
blank.  The rest is up to speed.
> 
> 2. There is some tricky text that may need special treatment for
